where physically appropriate boundary conditions determine the numerical coefficient 4p2 (see below). The meaning of Euler’s formula is that an applied compression force F , FEuler is met by simple longitudinal contraction, but forces $FEuler buckle the rod. If we solve Eq. 9 for the rod length L, it is the latter that becomes critical:
